{"ts":"2026-06-30T15:52:28.052Z","author":"claude-code-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-g61e"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"AGENTS.md: mandate reading full live pm item data (status/resolution/comments) before any state claim"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Add a top-priority Non-Negotiable + Working Rule to AGENTS.md requiring agents to read the FULL current data of every relevant pm item (status, resolution, close_reason, expected/actual_result, all comments, notes, history) via pm get/pm comments BEFORE making or repeating ANY claim about its state, and to NEVER report a feature/release/fix/blocker as blocked/broken/working/done from memory, a prior summary, or a recalled system-reminder. Live pm data cross-checked against the real system (npm view, gh run/release list, workflow files) wins over stale memory. Trigger: in the 2026-06-30 PR#408 session the agent wrongly reported the daily auto-release as 'blocked (RELEASE_PAT absent)' from stale memory, when pm-9gxi was already CLOSED (RELEASE_PAT configured, v2026.6.30 published to npm latest + GitHub Releases). Prevents recurrence."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Chore"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":1},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-guidance","area:docs","living-map","reliability"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-30T15:52:28.052Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-30T15:52:28.052Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"claude-code-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-u9d0"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"09c0eb564a351993100f08c173518e77e6383d0eeb83206f6357fb38809a9616","message":""}
